issues.title: B58 Engine Fuel Injector Failure
issues.description: Multiple fuel injectors failing prematurely, causing rough idle, misfiring, and potential engine damage. Common issue with the BMW B58 engine used in the GR Supra.
issues.fix_description: Replace faulty fuel injectors with updated parts, clear engine codes
issues.prevention: Use high quality fuel, regular oil changes, avoid extended idle periods

issues.title: ZF 8-Speed Transmission Harsh Shifting
issues.description: ZF 8HP automatic transmission experiencing harsh shifts, delayed engagement, or jerky operation, particularly during low-speed maneuvers.
issues.fix_description: Software update, transmission fluid change, or transmission rebuild in severe cases
issues.prevention: Regular transmission service, avoid aggressive driving during break-in period

issues.title: Paint Defects and Clear Coat Issues
issues.description: Various paint quality issues including orange peel texture, clear coat defects, and premature paint chipping, particularly on certain paint colors.
issues.fix_description: Professional paint correction, panel repainting, or full vehicle repaint in severe cases
issues.prevention: Regular washing and waxing, paint protection film installation

issues.title: Electronic Power Steering Failure
issues.description: Complete loss of power steering assistance due to electronic power steering system failure, creating dangerous driving conditions.
issues.fix_description: Replace EPS motor, steering rack, or control module depending on failure point
issues.prevention: Regular system diagnostics, avoid extreme steering inputs

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing
issues.description: BMW iDrive infotainment system freezing, becoming unresponsive, or displaying blank screen, affecting navigation and audio functions.
issues.fix_description: Software update, system reset, or head unit replacement in severe cases
issues.prevention: Regular software updates, avoid extreme temperatures

issues.title: Differential Whining Noise
issues.description: Rear differential producing whining or grinding noises during acceleration or deceleration, indicating potential bearing or gear wear.
issues.fix_description: Replace differential bearings, rebuild differential, or replace entire unit
issues.prevention: Regular differential fluid changes, avoid aggressive launches

issues.title: Turbocharger Waste Gate Actuator Failure
issues.description: Turbocharger wastegate actuator failing, causing overboost or underboost conditions, reduced performance, and potential engine damage.
issues.fix_description: Replace wastegate actuator or entire turbocharger assembly
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with quality oil, allow proper engine cool-down periods

issues.title: Brake Pedal Feel Issues
issues.description: Inconsistent brake pedal feel, spongy brakes, or excessive pedal travel affecting braking performance and driver confidence.
issues.fix_description: Brake fluid flush, brake system bleeding, or brake component replacement
issues.prevention: Regular brake fluid changes, quality brake fluid usage

issues.title: Air Conditioning Compressor Failure
issues.description: AC compressor failing prematurely, resulting in loss of air conditioning function and potential refrigerant leaks.
issues.fix_description: Replace AC compressor, evacuate and recharge system
issues.prevention: Regular AC system service, run AC periodically during winter

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Interior Trim Delamination
issues.description: Carbon fiber interior trim pieces experiencing delamination, bubbling, or separation of the carbon fiber layer from the base material.
issues.fix_description: Replace affected trim pieces with updated parts
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperatures, use interior protectants

issues.title: High Pressure Fuel Pump Failure
issues.description: High pressure fuel pump failing, causing fuel delivery issues, engine misfiring, and potential engine damage due to fuel starvation.
issues.fix_description: Replace high pressure fuel pump and associated components
issues.prevention: Use high quality fuel, regular fuel system cleaning

editorial.hero_blurb: The legendary Supra nameplate returns with German engineering under the hood. Toyota's partnership with BMW delivers a turbocharged inline-six that honors the heritage while embracing modern performance.
editorial.essence: This is the Supra reimagined through Bavarian precision and Japanese philosophy. The collaboration creates a focused sports car that prioritizes driving purity over outright power numbers.
editorial.heritage: After a 17-year hiatus, the fifth-generation Supra emerged from Toyota's partnership with BMW. Built on the same platform as the Z4, it carries forward the Supra's rear-wheel-drive sports car DNA while incorporating modern BMW powertrains.
editorial.design_philosophy: Clean, purposeful lines with aggressive proportions that communicate intent. Every curve serves aerodynamics or cooling, creating a form that's both respectful of Supra heritage and distinctly modern.
editorial.motorsport_history: The Supra name carries legendary status from IMSA GTO racing and Japanese touring car championships. While this generation is still building its competition resume, the nameplate's racing pedigree runs deep.
editorial.engine_character: The BMW-sourced B58 inline-six delivers smooth, linear power with a distinctive turbo whoosh. It's refined yet responsive, building boost progressively while maintaining the inline-six's inherent smoothness.
editorial.transmission_feel: The ZF 8-speed automatic shifts decisively with paddle commands, though it lacks the mechanical connection of a manual. Sport modes sharpen responses while comfort mode prioritizes smoothness.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Balanced and predictable with slight understeer at the limit. The short wheelbase creates nimble turn-in while the low center of gravity provides excellent stability through corners.
editorial.steering_feel: Electric power steering offers good on-center feel with decent feedback. While not telepathic, it communicates road surface changes and loading effectively, especially in Sport mode.
editorial.brake_confidence: Strong, progressive brakes with good pedal feel. The Brembo setup provides excellent stopping power with minimal fade during spirited driving sessions.
editorial.sound_signature: A sophisticated blend of turbo whistle and inline-six smoothness. The exhaust note is cultured rather than aggressive, with satisfying pops on overrun in Sport mode.
editorial.ideal_owner: Driving purists who appreciate balanced handling over straight-line speed. Perfect for those wanting a modern sports car with classic proportions and daily usability.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Manual transmission devotees or those seeking maximum power per dollar. Also not suited for those needing rear seats or significant cargo space.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for 2021+ models with the upgraded infotainment system. The 3.0-liter is the sweet spot for performance, offering strong acceleration with excellent refinement.

expertReviews.title: 2026 Toyota Supra Review | The FINAL Supra!
pros: Manual transmission available at no extra cost
Excellent acceleration at 3.9 seconds 0-60
Strong braking performance at 100ft stopping distance
Adaptive damping suspension standard on all trims
Beautiful exterior design with carbon fiber options
Comfortable seats suitable for long trips
Good cabin noise isolation
cons: Feels more road imperfections despite adaptive suspension
Poor rear visibility as expected for sports car
No rear seats
Limited cargo space at 10.2 cubic feet
Some wheel slip during acceleration with manual transmission
expertReviews.verdict: The 2026 Toyota Supra delivers impressive performance with its BMW-sourced 382hp twin-turbo inline-six, offering excellent acceleration and braking. The manual transmission is a highlight, shifting like butter with no price premium. While ride quality shows some road feel despite adaptive suspension, it's still comfortable for daily use. The MK5 Final Edition suggests this may be the last generation, making it potentially collectible. Direct competitor to Nissan Z with strong dynamics and premium features.

expertReviews.title: 2026 Toyota GR Supra MK5 Final Edition Track Drive Review!
pros: 382 HP B58 engine with 368 lb-ft torque
Great daily driver and track capability
Excellent ZF8 automatic and Toyota manual transmission
Well-planted handling and good brakes
Easy to modify platform
Refined interior
cons: Seats lack support for track driving
Floaty feeling at high speeds
Suspension could be stiffer from factory
Limited bolster adjustability
expertReviews.verdict: The 2026 Toyota GR Supra Final Edition is a well-rounded sports car that excels as both a daily driver and weekend track car. With 382 HP from the beloved B58 engine, improved chassis rigidity, and larger front brakes, it offers solid performance out of the box. While it has a slightly floaty feel at high speeds and seats that could be more supportive for track use, these issues are easily addressed with simple modifications. The car represents a fitting farewell to the Mark 5 generation - a platform that craves and responds well to modifications while being perfectly usable in stock form.

expertReviews.title: 2025 Toyota GR Supra Review: Power, Style & Innovation Unleashed!
pros: Two impressive engine options (255hp 4-cyl and 382hp 6-cyl)
Quick acceleration - 0-60 in 3.9 seconds with 3L engine
Near perfect 50/50 weight distribution and adaptive suspension
Premium interior with sport seats and 8.8-inch touchscreen
Comprehensive Toyota Safety Sense suite
Competitive pricing starting at $45,000
expertReviews.verdict: The 2025 Toyota GR Supra is positioned as a thrilling sports car that combines heritage, cutting-edge technology, and an unforgettable driving experience. With two engine options, refined design updates including new colors like plasma orange, and comprehensive safety features, it strikes a compelling balance between performance and value in the sports car segment.

expertReviews.title: 2025 Toyota GR Supra review: 0-100 & POV test drive
pros: Excellent powertrain combination - inline-6 turbo with rear-wheel drive
Superb 8-speed automatic transmission with perfect calibration and quick shifts
Outstanding handling and stability - one of the best handling sports cars on market
Wide torque band from 1,800-5,000 RPM with 500 Nm peak torque
Excellent traction and consistent predictable behavior
Good fuel economy averaging 12.5L/100km while driving hard
Intuitive infotainment system that remembers user preferences
Excellent brakes with big calipers and floating discs
BMW B58 engine known for reliability and tuning potential
cons: Fake engine sound pumped through speakers
Fake vents on body (bonnet, doors, front)
Tight interior space and small 290L boot capacity
Firm suspension may be uncomfortable for city driving
Limited practicality as a two-door sports car
expertReviews.verdict: The 2025 Toyota GR Supra is praised as an excellent driver's car with outstanding handling, a superb powertrain, and consistent performance. The reviewer considers it one of the best handling sports cars available, with particular praise for the transmission calibration and wide torque band. While it has some drawbacks like fake sound and limited practicality, it's recommended as potentially the last of its breed without hybrid technology or intrusive safety systems.

expertReviews.title: 2025 Toyota GR Supra Review: A Future Classic... Now
pros: Excellent 50/50 weight distribution and balanced handling
Perfect amount of power - 382hp feels manageable yet exciting
Great value at just over $70k for premium model
Daily driveable with adaptive dampers and comfort mode
Stunning looks that punch above price point
Engaging 6-speed manual transmission
Playful and fun character with slight rear slide capability
cons: Finicky BMW infotainment system
Too many fake vents on exterior
Exhaust too quiet - needs more sound
expertReviews.verdict: The 2025 Toyota GR Supra is a well-rounded sports car that hits above its price range. With 382hp from a turbocharged inline-6, perfect weight distribution, and engaging manual transmission, it delivers genuine sports car thrills while remaining daily-driveable. The reviewer believes it will become collectible and urges enthusiasts to buy now before it's too late, calling it one of the best sports cars in its class.

expertReviews.title: Toyota GR Supra Review | 6-Speed Manual, Rear Wheel Drive Sports Car
pros: Six-speed manual transmission with rev matching in sport mode
Authentic exhaust sound without fake audio pumped in
Driver-focused interior with separate climate controls and easy access buttons
Turbocharged 3L inline-six engine with 285 kW and 500 Nm torque
Multiple driving modes (sport/comfort) that transform the car's character
Stunning exterior design with aggressive styling and real exhausts
Good daily drivability when not in sport mode
Quality interior materials with leather and Alcantara throughout
cons: Cup holders interfere with manual gear shifting
Uncomfortable armrest area that doubles as cup holder space
Very narrow pedal setup causing feet to knock against each other
Limited practicality with only boot storage and no rear seats
Tight door storage - barely fits iPhone 14 Pro Max
Firm suspension in sport mode makes for bumpy ride
expertReviews.verdict: GET IT - The Toyota GR Supra manual is a brilliant driver-focused sports car that stands out with its unique styling and engaging driving experience. The 6-speed manual with rev matching, authentic exhaust sound, and well-designed driver controls make it a true enthusiast's car. Despite some interior ergonomic issues like poorly placed cup holders and narrow pedals, the car excels at its primary mission of providing an authentic sports car experience. Priced at 1.2 million rand, it's the entry point into the Supra range and delivers genuine sports car thrills.
